---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About QRSmith"
	description="QRSmith is a small, focused tool for generating styled QR codes with an embedded logo, entirely in your browser."
	canonicalPath="/about"
>
	<section class="mx-auto max-w-2xl">
		<h1 class="text-4xl font-700 tracking-tight text-[#2B2013]">About QRSmith</h1>

		<div class="mt-8 flex flex-col gap-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-[#5C4F3D]">
			<p>
				QRSmith does one thing: it turns a URL or a piece of text into a
				styled, scannable QR code, with your logo or initials embedded in
				the center if you want them. That's it. No account, no dashboard,
				no upsell funnel.
			</p>
			<p>
				We built it as a single-purpose tool on purpose. Most QR
				generators are buried inside a bloated "all-in-one" utility site
				with dozens of unrelated tools competing for space. QRSmith is
				just the QR generator &mdash; fast to load, easy to find, and
				easy to trust.
			</p>
			<p>
				Everything happens client-side, in your browser, using the
				open-source <strong class="font-semibold text-[#2B2013]">qr-code-styling</strong>
				library. The text you type, the image you upload, and the QR
				code it produces never touch a server. Nothing is stored,
				logged, or sent anywhere.
			</p>
			<p>
				QR codes have built-in error correction, which is what makes it
				safe to place a logo over the middle of the code &mdash; as long
				as the logo doesn't cover too much of the pattern, the code
				still scans reliably. QRSmith uses high error correction
				automatically whenever a logo is present.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
